        <p>Dear Graduating Students,</p>
        <p>We acknowledge that nothing can replace the traditional in-person Commencement ceremony that you all deserve. That is why the School is committed to providing a traditional Commencement ceremony when it is safe and feasible to do so, either in the Fall or at the following Commencement in June 2021. </p>
        <p>Presently, we are preparing to provide the best possible experience to recognize and honor all graduating BIOMED students’ outstanding growth and achievements. </p>
        <p><strong>1) Beginning Wednesday, June 10th,</strong> our <a href="https://drexel.edu/biomed/news-and-events/events-calendar/commencement-announcement/?utm_source=email&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=2020_commencement&utm_content=announcement"><strong style="color: #971b2f">BIOMED Class of 2020 Recognition &amp; Honors website</strong></a> will be available for all friends and family of graduating students. The website will include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Video message from the Dean (Paul Brandt-Rauf, ScD, MD, DrPH) </li>
          <li>Video messages from Associate Deans (Fred Allen, PhD and Andres Kriete, PhD)</li>
          <li>Video ‘Reading of the Names’ of all graduating BIOMED students</li>
          <li>Senior Design Showcase page</li>
          <li>Graduate Students Showcase page</li>
        </ul>
